-- Profuturo AFP Appoints Vicente Tuesta Head of Investments
-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 2012-10-03T21:56:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-03/profuturo-afp-appoints-vicente-tuesta-head-of-investments.html
Profuturo AFP,  Peru ’s fourth-largest
private pension provider, appointed Vicente Tuesta to replace
Pedro Grados as head of investments.  Tuesta was previously head of research at Prima AFP, the
country’s biggest pension fund manager. He has also held senior
research posts at Peru’s central bank and Deutsche Bank’s local
unit.  Grados was named chief executive officer of the Lima-based
company two months ago. Profuturo is a unit of Bank of  Nova
Scotia .  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in  Lima  at 
